aboration with Professor Jan Quinn's group (Newcastle University).</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The data could potentially be used by the pharmaceutical companies interested in developing antifungal therapies that target stress sensitivities in Candida albicans.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>8E85408D-7C64-4C8E-903F-C0F83EBECDC1</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Pharmaceuticals and Medical Biotechnology</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>http://www.abdn.ac.uk/ims/research/profiles/al.brown</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/B837AED6-2FA3-49ED-943D-51002FB9309E"><gtr:id>B837AED6-2FA3-49ED-943D-51002FB9309E</gtr:id><gtr:title>Metabolism in fungal pathogenesis.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Cold Spring Harbor perspectives in medicine</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a723c8188e6fbf5f179ad6d78b429d57"><gtr:id>a723c8188e6fbf5f179ad6d78b429d57</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Ene IV</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>2157-1422</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/2D392725-69CD-4562-A63B-44B2BA136F50"><gtr:id>2D392725-69CD-4562-A63B-44B2BA136F50</gtr:id><gtr:title>Stress adaptation in a pathogenic fungus.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>The Journal of experimental biology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/d76cfcb6a99c404003e1ff349c33165e"><gtr:id>d76cfcb6a99c404003e1ff349c33165e</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Brown AJ</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0022-0949</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="h